Kibra MP aspirant Rosemary Odinga is admitted in hospital with a brain tumour, but her life is not in danger, a doctor has said.Non-cancerous brain tumourRosemary, the daughter of Cord leader Raila Odinga, is admitted at the Aga Khan University Hospital, where she is being monitored before she undergoes surgery to have the meningioma &mdash; a non-cancerous tumour &mdash; removed.One doctor, speaking to the Star on condition of anonymity, said the tumor is usually harmless but it applies pressure on the brain though it is not life-threatening.The second born in Raila&rsquo;s family, Rosemary was first admitted at Aga Khan on Friday with a headache and moved to Nairobi Hospital on Sunday.The source said she had been in the hospital&rsquo;s Intensive Care Unit before she was moved yesterday morning.Other sources close to Rosemary said her hospital records were untraceable and that only family members were allowed to visit.The source said only immediate family members are being allowed to visit.Bid for kibra mpIn January, Rosemary announced she will run for Kibra MP.Her father was the Lang&rsquo;ata MP from 1992 to February 2013, before the constituency was split into Kibra and Lang&rsquo;ata for the March 4, 2013, general election.Her older brother Fidel Odinga died on January 4, 2015. Her younger siblings are Winnie Odinga and Raila Odinga Jnr.Rosemary is known for being the only snail farmer in East Africa.Since June 2015, as the patron of Key Empowerment Foundation Kenya, she has been at the forefront of facilitating youth and women to apply for and get birth certificates and ID cards to enable them to fully access government services.